measure.description:
T-score shows how much bone mineral density (BMD) is higher or lower than the bone density of a healthy 30-year old adult.
According to the World Health Organization (WHO):
T-score of -1.0 or above= normal bone density;
T-score between -1.0 and -2.5 means = osteopenia;
T-score of -2.5 or below = osteoporosis.

